  "classFeatures": [
    {
      "name": "Ranger's Focus",
      "description": "Spend Hope and make an attack with your weapon. On a success, you temporarily put your Ranger's Focus on the target along with doing damage from the attack. While they are your focus:\n\n- You know precisely what direction they are in.\n\n- All damage rolls you make against them add +1d6.\n\n- When you miss them with an attack, you can end Ranger's Focus to reroll your Duality dice and take the new result.\n\nOnly one creature can be your Focus at a time."
    }
  ],
  "backgroundQuestions": [
    "A terrible creature hurt your community, and you've vowed to hunt it down. What is it, and what unique trail or sign does it leave behind anywhere it goes?",
